item.title: [PI] Is there a fix to the Int[] Memory Leak?
item.dc:creator: @_synchronized ~synchronized
item.description:
@_synchronized wrote:

Memory leaks are caused when the garbage collector is called when it is not needed. Most private servers call the garbage collector when truly it doesn’t have to be used, e.g System.gc() will remove any unnecessary objects.
